description: Retrieves a list of the keys in the Key Vault as JSON Web Key structures that contain the public part of a deleted key. This operation includes deletion-specific information. The Get Deleted Keys operation is applicable for vaults enabled for soft-delete. While the operation can be invoked on any vault, it will return an error if invoked on a non soft-delete enabled vault. This operation requires the keys/list permission.

deleteddate.description: The time when the key was deleted, in UTC

scheduledpurgedate.description: The time when the key is scheduled to be purged, in UTC

tags.description: Application specific metadata in the form of key-value pairs.

maxresults.description: Maximum number of results to return in a page. If not specified the service will return up to 25 results.

managed.description: True if the key's lifetime is managed by key vault. If this is a key backing a certificate, then managed will be true.

recoveryid.description: The url of the recovery object, used to identify and recover the deleted key.
